When a Grip enters the Spacing Zone:$NMove the Rope Count into .BC$NCalculate the Grip Spacing Error .GSE$NCalculate the distance of rope that needs to pass in the spacing zone.  $N$NIf the Spacing Pointer is set to 0 then the lift does not know where Grip 1 is.  The Spacing will treat all cabins as perfectly spaced until Cabin One enters the spacing zone.  At this point it will use the last values in the Spacing Array.  When Grip One enters the Spacing Zone for the Second time the Spacer will know the rope length and will be able to calculate the nominal Spacing Distance between grips.
